9 An Act relating to credit unions; amending 6 O.S.
2021, Sections 2001, 2001.1, 2006, 2007, and 2010,
10 which relate to definitions, the Oklahoma State
Credit Union Board, succession, membership, and the
11 board of directors; defining term; requiring powers
exercised by the Board to ensure certain competitive
12 charter; allowing certain credit union to make loans
to its members with certain flexibility; allowing
13 certain credit unions to invest certain shares,
stocks, or member units of certain companies under a
14 certain percentage of net worth of certain credit
union; prohibiting the Oklahoma State Credit Union
15 Board from considering certain overlap when
determining certain approval; allowing the Board to
16 permit certain credit union to add certain category
of association; allowing certain records to be filed
17 with the Bank Commissioner within a certain time
frame; allowing certain board of directors and
18 members to receive certain compensation; requiring
certain compensations to be disclosed annually in
19 certain report; updating statutory references; making
language gender neutral; updating statutory language;
20 and providing an effective date.
21
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
24
SB1623 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 6 O.S. 2021, Section 2001, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 2001. As used in this chapter Section 2001 et seq. of
4 this title:
5 1. “Credit union” means a cooperative nonprofit society
6 incorporated for the purpose of promoting thrift among its members,
7 and creating a source of credit for them at legitimate rates of
8 interest for provident or productive purposes; and
9 2. “Credit union organization” means any organization that is
10 established primarily to serve the needs of credit unions and whose
11 business relates to the daily operations of the credit unions served
12 by such credit union organization;
13 3. “Paid-in and unimpaired capital and surplus” means, the
14 balance of all paid-in share accounts and other deposits, less any
15 loss for which no reserve has been established or which has not been
16 charged against undivided earnings, plus the credit balance (or, or
17 less the debit balance) balance, of undivided earnings, after all
18 losses have been provided for and net earnings or net losses have
19 been added thereto or deducted therefrom. Reserves shall not be
20 considered as a part of surplus; and
21 4. “Underserved areas” means the same as provided for in 12
22 U.S.C., Section 1759.
23 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 6 O.S. 2021, Section 2001.1, is
24 amended to read as follows:
SB1623 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Section 2001.1. A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma State
2 Credit Union Board, which shall consist of five (5) members
3 appointed by the Governor. The State Bank Commissioner shall be one
4 of the members, and he or she shall preside as Chairman Chair of the
5 Oklahoma State Credit Union Board. One of the other four members
6 shall be a member of a credit union organized under the laws of this
7 state, and each of the other three members shall be the officer in
8 charge of operations or a director of a credit union organized under
9 the laws of this state; provided, however, one of those three may be
10 from a federal credit union. Said Such four members shall be
11 selected by the Governor, with advice and consent of the Senate,
12 from a list of not less than five (5) names for each member to be
13 appointed submitted by the Oklahoma Credit Union League. The
14 members appointed by the Governor shall serve for terms of four (4),
15 three (3), two (2) and one (1) year, respectively. Upon the
16 expiration of the terms of the four members previously appointed by
17 the Governor pursuant to the provisions of this section, their
18 successors shall be appointed for terms of four (4) years. If a
19 member of the Oklahoma State Credit Union Board ceases to hold the
20 qualifications required for the appointment of such member, then the
21 remaining members shall immediately declare the office of such
22 member vacant and such member shall cease to be a member of the
23 Oklahoma State Credit Union Board. Any vacancy in the membership of
24 the State Credit Union Board, caused by other than the expiration of
SB1623 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 a te rm, shall be filled only for the balance of the term of the
2 member in whose position the vacancy occurs. Appointment made to
3 fill a vacancy shall be made by the Governor, with advice and
4 consent of the Senate, from a list of not less than five (5) names
5 submitted by the Oklahoma Credit Union League. Except as otherwise
6 provided in this section, members shall serve until their terms
7 expire or until their successors are appointed and qualified.
8 B. Each member of the State Credit Union Board shall be
9 entitled to be reimbursed for necessary travel expenses pursuant to
10 the State Travel Reimbursement Act.
11 C. The State Banking Department shall provide such clerical,
12 technical and legal assistance as the State Credit Union Board may
13 require.
14 D. Powers exercised by the Board may be executed in a manner to
15 ensure a competitive state credit union charter.
16 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 6 O.S. 2021, Section 2006, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 2006. A credit union shall have succession in its
19 corporate name during its existence and shall have power:
20 1. To make contracts;
21 2. To sue and be sued;
22 3. To adopt and use a common seal and alter the same at
23 pleasure;
24
