4 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 6 O.S. 2021, Section 2007, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 2007. A. Credit union membership shall consist of the
7 incorporators, and such other persons and incorporated and
8 unincorporated organizations and their employees, as may be elected
9 to membership. Each member shall subscribe to at least one share of
10 the credit union’s stock and pay the entrance fee. Credit union
11 membership shall be limited to groups having a common bond of
12 occupation or association, which shall be limited to one of the
13 following categories:
14 1. Groups that have the same common bond of occupation or
15 association;
16 2. Persons or organizations within a well-defined community,
17 neighborhood or rural district; or
18 3. Groups which have, as to each individual group, a common
19 bond of occupation or association, but, as to all such groups, need
20 not have the same common bond of occupation or association as other
21 groups within the credit union.
22 B. The Oklahoma State Credit Union Board may not consider
23 overlap in determining approval of a proposed field of membership
24 for a credit union chartered by this state.
SB1623 HFLR Page 17
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 C. The Board may permit a credit union chartered by this state
2 to add any category of association as is preapproved by the National
3 Credit Union Administration and may designate other preapproved
4 categories of associations or persons eligible for membership
5 including, but not limited to, persons with income at or below one
6 hundred fifty percent (150%) of the United States Department of
7 Health and Human Services Poverty Guidelines residing in underserved
8 areas.
9 D. A central credit union may be organized to which members of
10 existing credit unions operating in accordance with the law of the
11 State of Oklahoma this state, or of the United States of America,
12 may belong, and to which credit unions organized and operating under
13 the State of Oklahoma this state or of the United States of America
14 may also belong.
15 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 6 O.S. 2021, Section 2010, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 2010. A. 1. The business affairs of a credit union
18 shall be managed by a board of not less than seven (7) members,
19 elected by the members of the credit union, from their number, at
20 their annual meeting, the organizational meeting being the first
21 annual meeting, and to hold office for such terms as the bylaws may
22 provide.
23 2. The bylaws of a credit union shall not prevent or restrict a
24 member from serving as a director, unless such member has been, or
SB1623 HFLR Page 18
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 is l ater, convicted of a crime involving dishonesty or breach of
2 trust.
3 3. A record of names and addresses of the board of directors
4 and the respective committees and officers shall be filed with the
5 Bank Commissioner within ten (10) days after their election. No
6 member of the board of directors shall, as such, be compensated, but
7 the officers elected by the board of directors and the members of
8 the credit and supervisory committees may receive such compensation
9 for services performed as the board shall, by resolution, authorize.
10 4. The board of directors shall meet at least once a month,
11 unless permitted by the Bank Commissioner to meet less often, and
12 shall have the general direction and control of the affairs of the
13 corporation. The minutes of all such meetings shall be kept. Among
14 other things they shall act upon applications for membership.
15 5. The board shall also:
16 a. declare dividends and determine rates of interest on
17 deposits,
18 b. fill vacancies in the board and in the credit
19 committee until successors elected at the next annual
20 meeting have qualified,
21 c. authorize investment of credit union funds other than
22 loans to members,
23 d. determine from time to time the maximum number of
24 shares and deposits that will be accepted from a
