BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 pend ing applications for membership at each regular meeting of the
2 board of directors.
3 C. 1. A credit committee of not less than three members shall
4 be either elected by the members or appointed by the board of
5 directors, from the membership of the credit union, at the annual
6 meeting of the members, or at the first meeting of the board of
7 directors after the annual meeting of the members, as the bylaws may
8 provide. Members of the credit committee shall hold office for such
9 terms as specified in the bylaws. In lieu of a credit committee, a
10 credit manager may be appointed by the board of directors, if the
11 bylaws so provide. The credit manager shall be an officer of the
12 credit union.
13 2. A credit committee, or if the bylaws so provide, a credit
14 manager, shall have the general supervision of all loans to members.
15 It shall be the duty of the credit committee, or if applicable, the
16 credit manager, to provide for the review of all applications for
17 loans, to ascertain whether or not such loan would benefit the
18 applicant, and to determine whether or not the security offered, in
19 the judgment of the credit committee or the credit manager, is
20 sufficient and the terms proper. If the loans of the credit union
21 are supervised by a credit committee, the credit committee shall
22 meet as often as may be required after due notice has been given to
23 each member thereof, but not less than once a month, and shall keep
24 a record of all meetings.
SB1623 HFLR Page 22
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 3. The credit committee, or the credit manager, shall make a
2 report to the members at the annual meeting.
3 4. To facilitate the work of the credit committee or the credit
4 manager, the credit committee or the credit manager, whichever is
5 applicable, may appoint one or more loan officers and assistants, as
6 may be necessary. Loan officers shall act under the direction of
7 the credit committee or the credit manager and may approve or
8 disapprove loans, but only within written rules and regulations
9 established by the credit committee or the credit manager. A record
10 of loans approved by each loan officer shall be made available upon
