12 D. 1. The supervisory committee shall be appointed by the
13 board of directors unless otherwise provided in the bylaws. One
14 director may be appointed or elected to the supervisory committee,
15 but not the treasurer.
16 2. The supervisory committee shall make a semiannual
17 examination of the affairs of the credit union, including an audit
18 of its books; and shall make an annual audit and a report to be
19 submitted at the annual meeting of the corporation. However, if the
20 supervisory committee, with the approval of the board of directors,
21 employs an auditor approved by the Oklahoma State Credit Union
22 Board, a licensed public accountant or a certified public accountant
23 to perform an annual audit of the affairs and books of the credit
