1 5. 6. The supervisory committee shall in such manner as it
2 deems advisable cause the accounts of the members to be verified
3 with the records of the treasurer from time to time and not less
4 frequently than once every two (2) years.
5 6. 7. The supervisory committee shall meet as often as
6 necessary to conduct the business of the supervisory committee and
7 at such other times as the Commissioner may prescribe. Minutes of
8 all such meetings shall be kept.
9 7. 8. No member of the supervisory committee may be excluded
10 from attending the meetings of the board of directors of the credit
11 union.
12 SECTION 6. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
13
14 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT OVERSIGHT, dated
04/15/2026 - DO PASS.
